OL,3,CSister remembers teenage brother
OL,4,Ckilled in Omagh atrocity
OL,6,FDuring her evidence to the probe she
OL,7,Falso shared remarks from the rest of
OL,8,Fher family, including from her sister
OL,9,FElaine who said their family had been
OL,10,Fbroken beyond repair by Alan's murder,
OL,11,Fadding: "There is no way of healing
OL,12,Four hearts."
OL,14,FThe teenager had been in Omagh with
OL,15,Fhis mother to help her with the
OL,16,Fshopping, and was also set to open a
OL,17,Fbank account as he prepared for the
OL,18,Fnext stage of his life.
