OL,3,CSister remembers teenage brother
OL,4,Ckilled in Omagh atrocity
OL,6,FThe inquiry heard his family received
OL,7,Fhis GCSE results days after his death
OL,8,Fand how he had been due to go to
OL,9,Fcatering college.
OL,11,FMs Hayes, who is just six months
OL,12,Fyounger than Alan, said they had been
OL,13,Fvery close, describing him as her
OL,14,F"other half".
OL,16,F"Me and Alan were so close in age that
OL,17,Feverything in life we shared... we
OL,18,Fwalked down the road to school
OL,19,Ftogether, we came home together, we
OL,20,Fshared every part of our life," she
OL,21,Ftold the inquiry.
OL,26,@vD@AOUvD@LO]xD@AOU|D@_O]
