OL,3,CSister remembers teenage brother
OL,4,Ckilled in Omagh atrocity
OL,6,F"He had named me Sissa, just Alan's
OL,7,Fwee way of speaking to me."
OL,9,FShe also paid tribute to his
OL,10,Fdedication to their mother, helping
OL,11,Fher with the grocery shopping every
OL,12,Fweek, and even taking her to see the
OL,13,Fmovie Titanic in the cinema which he
OL,14,Fhad been really excited about.
OL,16,F"Other teenage boys would have been
OL,17,Fout with friends or mucking out at the
OL,18,Fpark, Alan had so much dedication to
OL,19,Four mother that he went every Saturday
OL,20,Fwith her into the town to help her
OL,21,Fcarry the shopping home," she said.
