OL,3,CSister remembers teenage brother
OL,4,Ckilled in Omagh atrocity
OL,6,F"He was so loving, so compassionate
OL,7,Fwith everybody. He had no malice, not
OL,8,Fa bad bone in his body, just wanted a
OL,9,Fbetter life for not only himself but
OL,10,Ffor everybody else who was around him."
OL,12,FShe said his compassion went beyond
OL,13,Ftheir family to helping their
OL,14,Fneighbours, even cutting lawns despite
OL,15,Fhaving an allergy to grass.
OL,17,FMs Hayes recalled the last time she
OL,18,Fever saw her brother getting ready to
OL,19,Fgo into Omagh with their mother.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@gO]
