OL,3,CSister remembers teenage brother
OL,4,Ckilled in Omagh atrocity
OL,6,F"I said 'Alan, remember to get your
OL,7,Fhair cut today, number two around the
OL,8,Fsides and get it cut on top, and for
OL,9,FGod's sake remember to buy gel', he
OL,10,Fsaid, 'yeah, ok Sissa, I love you,
OL,11,FI'll see you later'," she said.
OL,13,F"I watched them walking up the path...
OL,14,Fthat was the last time I ever seen him
OL,15,Falive."
OL,17,FThe inquiry also heard a statement by
OL,18,Fhis teacher Carol Porter at Gibson
OL,19,FPrimary School who recalled Alan's
OL,20,Finfectious smile, love for his family
OL,21,Fand sense of humour.
