OL,3,CSister remembers teenage brother
OL,4,Ckilled in Omagh atrocity
OL,6,FIn December 1997 he returned on work
OL,7,Fplacement to help her in the school,
OL,8,Fsaying she was "absolutely delighted"
OL,9,Fto have him back, saying he had helped
OL,10,Fin every way leading up to the
OL,11,FChristmas show.
OL,13,FMs Porter said when she became aware
OL,14,FAlan had been murdered in the bomb she
OL,15,Ffelt a horrendous feeling of absolute
OL,16,Fshock for days.
OL,18,F"It turned into total sadness and
OL,19,Fanger, why did Alan and all the other
OL,20,Finnocent victims do, what did they do
OL,21,Fto deserve that, absolutely nothing.
OL,26,@pD@POUpD@eO]zD@AOU
