OL,3,CSister remembers teenage brother
OL,4,Ckilled in Omagh atrocity
OL,6,F"I will never forget going back to
OL,7,Fschool 10 days after the bomb and just
OL,8,Fbroke down into tears, the memories of
OL,9,FAlan as a child and much more recently
OL,10,Fin the previous December just came
OL,11,Fflooding in.
OL,13,F"It was something that haunts me and
OL,14,Fit will live with me forever."
OL,16,FInquiry chairman Lord Turnbull thanked
OL,17,FMs Hayes for coming to the inquiry and
OL,18,Fspeaking "so eloquently" about Alan as
OL,19,Fa "much loved and loving son, brother
OL,20,Fand uncle".
